JOHANNESBURG Dondo Mogajane s appointment as National Treasury s new director-general continued to receive praise on Friday, with the Black Business Council (BBC) welcoming it and wishing him success in his new role. Congratulations to Dondo Mogajane, confirmed as the new DG for SA Treasury. Ensures continuity and much needed institutional memory pic.twitter.com/4UyKEXTjJF His immediate appointment by the Minister of Finance, Mr [Malusi] Gigaba, clearly demonstrates that indeed the Minister has a commitment and an urgency to advance South African Economic growth, BBC President Danisa Baloyi said.National Treasury announced Mogajane s appointment on Wednesday after Cabinet confirmed his appointment.Mogajane succeeds Lungile Fuzile who last month asked to be released from his duties a year before his contract could come to an end in May 2018 following the Cabinet reshuffle at the end of March.Mogajane, who was the deputy director-general responsible for the public finance division, had been acting in the position since Fuzile s departure. Cabinet appoints Dondo Mogajane as Treasury director-general, reports @LindaEnsor https://t.co/wy6Pzke5dY pic.twitter.com/aaZO7bHkHcHe has also been involved in the CEO Initiative, where he worked very closely with the BBC on behalf of National Treasury.BBC secretary general, George Sebulela, said Mogajane was indeed not new to the BBC. He has been a team leader for a BBC and National Treasury committee that was appointed by former Minister Pravin Gordan to address our concerns with regards to our Radical Economic Transformation requirements that National Treasury will assist to implement, Sebulela said. Fedusa: New National Treasury DG Dondo Mogajane is a highly qualified bureaucrat that has served with distinction, dedication since 1999. pic.twitter.com/DgeLJLV1qt African News Agency